    "content_hash": "5653c04d68135a4e",
    "department": "Finance",
    "description": "OVERVIEW\n\nCoinTracker https://www.cointracker.io/ makes cryptocurrency portfolio tracking and tax compliance simple. CoinTracker enables consumers and businesses to seamlessly track their cryptocurrency portfolio, investment performance, taxes, and more. We are a globally distributed team on a mission to enable everyone in the world to use crypto with peace of mind. Learn more https://www.notion.so/cointracker/CoinTracker-is-Hiring-7308c712493940a3b6e62257d283dad8 about our mission, culture, and hiring process.\n\n\n\nSOME THINGS WE’RE PROUD OF\n\n - 🛠️ Building foundational tools in the cryptocurrency space\n\n - 📄 Over 1M tax forms generated\n\n - 💲 $80B+ in cryptocurrency is tracked on CoinTracker (~over 5% of the entire crypto market)\n\n - 🤝 Partnered with Coinbase, H\u0026R Block, Intuit TurboTax, MetaMask, OpenSea, Phantom, Solana, and Uniswap\n\n - 🗺️ Founders: Jon https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonlerner/ previously built TextNow (200M downloads), Chandan https://www.linkedin.com/in/clodha/ was previously a product manager at Google \u0026 Google[x]\n\n - 💼 $100M+ venture capital raised from Accel, General Catalyst, Y Combinator, Initialized Capital, Coinbase Ventures, Kraken Ventures, Intuit Ventures, 776 Ventures, Balaji Srinivasan https://twitter.com/balajis, Claire Hughes Johnson https://twitter.com/chughesjohnson, Gokul Rajaram https://twitter.com/gokulr, Serena Williams https://twitter.com/serenawilliams, Zach Perret https://twitter.com/zachperret\n\n - 🌴 Awesome benefits https://www.notion.so/cointracker/Benefits-b5db95c6d3224ab1ae3a384048cbaee3\n\n\nYOUR MISSION\n\nServe as the CEO's strategic partner, leading the Finance function while driving insights and decisions that accelerate CoinTracker's growth and long-term success.\n\n\nYOUR ONE-YEAR OUTCOMES\n\n - Strategic partnership with the CEO. You proactively surface insights, challenge assumptions, and bring strategic options the company wasn't considering. Decision quality improves as a result.\n\n - Clear view of growth levers. Partnership economics, pricing, channel performance, and customer unit economics are well-understood and actively used to drive strategy.\n\n - Smooth finance operations. Forecasting, board reporting, and financial planning happen on time and at high quality.\n\n\nWHAT YOU WILL DO\n\n - Partner with the CEO on company strategy, capital allocation, and key business decisions.\n\n - Own financial planning, forecasting, and board/investor reporting.\n\n - Drive strategic analysis on partnerships, pricing, market opportunities, and M\u0026A.\n\n - Lead and develop a small finance team (Strategic Finance, Controller).\n\n - Push into adjacent areas (data, growth analytics, market analysis) where finance perspective adds leverage.\n\n - Build the analytical foundation for understanding unit economics, cohort performance, and growth drivers.\n\n\nWHAT WE LOOK FOR\n\n - Role-agnostic\n   \n   - Impact: Demonstrated ability to drive outsized business impact.\n   \n   - Mission alignment: Strong personal conviction in crypto; hungry to make progress on our mission of enabling everyone to use crypto with peace of mind.\n   \n   - Trust: Say what you believe. Do what you say. Take ownership broadly.\n   \n   - Communication: Clear and concise; able to zoom in on details and zoom out to strategy.\n\n - Role-specific\n   \n   - 10+ years of experience in strategic finance, FP\u0026A, or related roles.\n   \n   - Experience at a high-growth SaaS or tech company ($30M-$200M revenue scale).\n   \n   - Strong analytical and modeling skills; can go deep on data.\n   \n   - Excellent executive communication; board-ready.\n   \n   - Experience managing a small team.\n   \n   - Proactive, strategic thinker who brings insights without being asked.\n   \n   - Comfortable with ambiguity and structuring messy problems.\n\n - Nice to haves\n   \n   - IB/PE background followed by operating experience.\n   \n   - Experience at a crypto company or has personal meaningful involvement in crypto on the side.\n   \n   - Background in consumer subscription or B2B SaaS.\n\nThe starting salary for this position is between $240,000 - $280,000 USD. Candidate's location does not impact the posted salary range. The actual compensation offered will be based on a variety of job-related factors including relevant skills, education, and experience. This position also includes equity in CoinTracker and benefits like medical, dental, vision, 401(k), life insurance, and PTO.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
